obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (20640)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20640&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Securitisation and`
  line `Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 21st day of June, 2002.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (20641)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20641&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) Appellate Tribunal means a Debts Recovery Appellate Tribunal established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 8 of the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and Financial Institutions Act,`
  line `1993 (51 of 1993);`
  line
  line `(b) asset reconstruction means acquisition by any ^1`
  line `[asset reconstruction company]of any right`
  line `or interest of any bank or financial institution in any financial assistance for the purpose of realisation`
  line `of such financial assistance;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ba) asset reconstruction company means a company registered with Reserve Bank under`
  line `section 3 for the purposes of carrying on the business of asset reconstruction or securitisation, or`
  line both;]
  line
  line `(c) bank means--`
  line
  line `(i) a banking company; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a corresponding new bank; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the State Bank of India; or`
  line
  line `(iv) a subsidiary bank; or`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(iva) a multi-State co-operative bank; or]`
  line
  line `(v) such other bank which the Central Government may, by notification, specify for the`
  line `purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) banking company shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (c) of section 5 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(e) Board means the Securities and Exchange Board of India established under section 3 of the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992);`
  line
  line `(f) borrower means ^4[any person who, or a pooled investment vehicle as defined in clause (da)`
  line `of section 2 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) which,] has been granted financial assistance by any bank or`
  line `financial institution or who has given any guarantee or created any mortgage or pledge as security for`
  line `the financial assistance granted by any bank or financial institution ^5[and includes a person who, or a pooled investment vehicle which,]`
  line `becomes borrower of a ^6`
  line `[asset reconstruction company]consequent upon acquisition by it of any`
  line `rights or interest of any bank or financial institution in relation to such financial assistance^7`
  line `[or who`
  line `has raised funds through issue of debt securities];`
  line
  line `(g) Central Registry means the registry set up or cause to be set up under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 20;`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(ga) company means a company as defined in clause (20) of section 2 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);]`
  line
  line `(h) corresponding new bank shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (da) of section 5 of`
  line `the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line ^8
  line `[(ha) debt shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (g) of section 2 of the Recovery of`
  line `Debts Due to Banks and Financial Institutions Act, 1993 (51 of 1993) and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) unpaid portion of the purchase price of any tangible asset given on hire or financial lease`
  line `or conditional sale or under any other contract;`
  line
  line `(ii) any right, title or interest on any intangible asset or licence or assignment of such`
  line `intangible asset, which secures the obligation to pay any unpaid portion of the purchase price of`
  line `such intangible asset or an obligation incurred or credit otherwise extended to enable any`
  line `borrower to acquire the intangible asset or obtain licence of such asset;]`
  line
  line `(i) Debts Recovery Tribunal means the Tribunal established under sub-section (1) of section 3`
  line `of the Recovery of Debts due to Banks and Financial Institutions Act, 1993 (51 of 1993);`
  line
  line ^9
  line `[(ia) debt securities means debt securities listed in accordance with the regulations made by`
  line `the Board under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act,1992 (15 of 1992);]`
  line
  line ^10
  line `[(j) default means--`
  line
  line `(i) non-payment of any debt or any other amount payable by the borrower to any secured`
  line `creditor consequent upon which the account of such borrower is classified as non-performing`
  line `asset in the books of account of the secured creditor; or`
  line
  line `(ii) non-payment of any debt or any other amount payable by the borrower with respect to`
  line `debt securities after notice of ninety days demanding payment of dues served upon such borrower`
  line `by the debenture trustee or any other authority in whose favour security interest is created for the`
  line `benefit of holders of such debt securities;]`
  line
  line `(k) financial assistance means any loan or advance granted or any debentures or bonds`
  line `subscribed or any guarantees given or letters of credit established or any other credit facility extended`
  line `by any bank or financial institution^11`
  line `[including funds provided for the purpose of acquisition of any tangible asset on hire or financial lease or conditional sale or under any other contract or obtaining`
  line `assignment or licence of any intangible asset or purchase of debt securities;]`
  line
  line `(l) financial asset means debt or receivables and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a claim to any debt or receivables or part thereof, whether secured or unsecured; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any debt or receivables secured by, mortgage of, or charge on, immovable property; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a mortgage, charge, hypothecation or pledge of movable property; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any right or interest in the security, whether full or part underlying such debt or`
  line `receivables; or`
  line
  line `(v) any beneficial interest in property, whether movable or immovable, or in such debt,`
  line `receivables, whether such interest is existing, future, accruing, conditional or contingent; or`
  line
  line ^12
  line `[(va) any beneficial right, title or interest in any tangible asset given on hire or financial lease`
  line `or conditional sale or under any other contract which secures the obligation to pay any unpaid`
  line `portion of the purchase price of such asset or an obligation incurred or credit otherwise provided`
  line `to enable the borrower to acquire such tangible asset; or`
  line
  line `(vb) any right, title or interest on any intangible asset or licence or assignment of such`
  line `intangible asset, which secures the obligation to pay any unpaid portion of the purchase price of`
  line `such intangible asset or an obligation incurred or credit otherwise extended to enable the`
  line `borrower to acquire such intangible asset or obtain licence of the intangible asset; or]`
  line
  line `(vi) any financial assistance;`
  line
  line `(m)financial institution means--`
  line
  line `(i) a public financial institution within the meaning of section 4A of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(ii) any institution specified by the Central Government under sub-clause (ii) of clause (h) of`
  line `section 2 of the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and Financial Institutions Act, 1993`
  line `(51 of 1993);`
  line
  line `(iii) the International Finance Corporation established under the International Finance`
  line `Corporation (Status, Immunities and Privileges ) Act, 1958 (42 of 1958);`
  line
  line ^13
  line `[(iiia) a debenture trustee registered with the Board and appointed for secured debt`
  line securities;
  line
  line `(iiib) asset reconstruction company, whether acting as such or managing a trust created for`
  line `the purpose of securitisation or asset reconstruction, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(iv) any other institution or non-banking financial company as defined in clause (f) of section`
  line `45-I of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), which the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify as financial institution for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line ^14
  line `[(ma) financial lease means a lease under any lease agreement of tangible asset, other than`
  line `negotiable instrument or negotiable document, for transfer of lessor's right therein to the lessee for a`
  line `certain time in consideration of payment of agreed amount periodically and where the lessee becomes`
  line `the owner of the such assets at the expiry of the term of lease or on payment of the agreed residual`
  line `amount, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(n) hypothecation means a charge in or upon any movable property, existing or future, created`
  line `by a borrower in favour of a secured creditor without delivery of possession of the movable property`
  line `to such creditor, as a security for financial assistance and includes floating charge and crystallization`
  line `of such charge into fixed charge on movable property;`
  line
  line ^15
  line `[(na) negotiable document means a document, which embodies a right to delivery of tangible`
  line `assets and satisfies the requirements for negotiability under any law for the time being in force`
  line `including warehouse receipt and bill of lading;]`
  line
  line `(o) non-performing asset means an asset or account of a borrower, which has been classified by`
  line `a bank or financial institution as sub-standard, ^16`
  line `[doubtful or loss asset,`
  line
  line `(a) in case such bank or financial institution is administered or regulated by any authority or`
  line `body established, constituted or appointed by any law for the time being in force, in accordance`
  line `with the directions or guidelines relating to assets classifications issued by such authority or body;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, in accordance with the directions or guidelines relating to assets`
  line `classifications issued by the Reserve Bank];`
  line
  line `(p) notification means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(q) obligor means a person liable to the originator, whether under a contract or otherwise, to`
  line `pay a financial asset or to discharge any obligation in respect of a financial asset, whether existing,`
  line `future, conditional or contingent and includes the borrower;`
  line
  line `(r) originator means the owner of a financial asset which is acquired by a ^17`
  line `[asset reconstruction`
  line `company]for the purpose of securitisation or asset reconstruction;`
  line
  line `(s) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(t) property means--`
  line
  line `(i) immovable property;`
  line
  line `(ii) movable property;`
  line
  line `(iii) any debt or any right to receive payment of money, whether secured or unsecured;`
  line
  line `(iv) receivables, whether existing or future;`
  line
  line `(v) intangible assets, being know-how, patent, copyright, trade mark, licence, franchise or any`
  line `other business or commercial right of similar nature^18`
  line `[as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with Reserve Bank];`
  line
  line `(u)`
  line ^19
  line `[qualified buyer] means a financial institution, insurance company, bank, state`
  line `financial corporation, state industrial development corporation, ^20`
  line `[trustee or ^21`
  line `[asset reconstruction`
  line `company]which has been granted a certificate of registration under sub-section (4) of section 3 or`
  line `any asset management company making investment on behalf of mutual fund] or a foreign`
  line `institutional investor registered under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992`
  line `(15 of 1992) or regulations made thereunder,^22`
  line `[any category of non-institutional investors as may`
  line `be specified by the Reserve Bank under sub-section (1) of section 7] or any other body corporate`
  line `as may be specified by the Board;`
  line
  line ^13
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(w) Registrar of Companies means the Registrar defined in clause (40) of section 2 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(x) Reserve Bank means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(y) scheme means a scheme inviting subscription to security receipts proposed to be issued by a`
  line ^14
  line `[asset reconstruction company]under that scheme;`
  line
  line `(z) securitisation means acquisition of financial assets by any ^14`
  line `[asset reconstruction`
  line `company]from any originator, whether by raising of funds by such ^14`
  line `[asset reconstruction`
  line `company]from ^15`
  line `[qualified buyers]by issue of security receipts representing undivided interest in such`
  line `financial assets or otherwise;`
  line
  line ^13
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(zb) security agreement means an agreement, instrument or any other document or arrangement`
  line `under which security interest is created in favour of the secured creditor including the creation of`
  line `mortgage by deposit of title deeds with the secured creditor;`
  line
  line `(zc) secured asset means the property on which security interest is created;`
  line
  line ^16
  line `[(zd) secured creditor' means--`
  line
  line `(i) any bank or financial institution or any consortium or group of banks or financial`
  line `institutions holding any right, title or interest upon any tangible asset or intangible asset as`
  line `specified in clause (l);`
  line
  line `(ii) debenture trustee appointed by any bank or financial institution; or`
  line
  line `(iii) an asset reconstruction company whether acting as such or managing a trust set up by`
  line `such asset reconstruction company for the securitisation or reconstruction, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(iv) debenture trustee registered with ^17[the Board and appointed] for secured debt`
  line `securities; or`
  line
  line `(v) any other trustee holding securities on behalf of a bank or financial institution,`
  line `in whose favour security interest is created by any borrower for due repayment of any financial`
  line assistance.]
  line
  line `(ze) secured debt means a debt which is secured by any security interest;`
  line
  line ^18
  line `[(zf) security interest means right, title or interest of any kind, other than those specified in`
  line `section 31, upon property created in favour of any secured creditor and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any mortgage, charge, hypothecation, assignment or any right, title or interest of any kind,`
  line `on tangible asset, retained by the secured creditor as an owner of the property, given on hire or`
  line `financial lease or conditional sale or under any other contract which secures the obligation to pay`
  line `any unpaid portion of the purchase price of the asset or an obligation incurred or credit provided`
  line `to enable the borrower to acquire the tangible asset; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such right, title or interest in any intangible asset or assignment or licence of such`
  line `intangible asset which secures the obligation to pay any unpaid portion of the purchase price of`
  line `the intangible asset or the obligation incurred or any credit provided to enable the borrower to`
  line `acquire the intangible asset or licence of intangible asset;]`
  line
  line `(zg) security receipt means a receipt or other security, issued by a ^19`
  line `[asset reconstruction`
  line `company]to any ^20`
  line `[qualified buyer]pursuant to a scheme, evidencing the purchase oracquisition by the`
  line `holder thereof, of an undivided right, title orinterest in the financial asset involved in securitisation;`
  line
  line `(zh) sponsor means any person holding not less than ten per cent. of the paid-up equity capital`
  line `of a ^21`
  line `[asset reconstruction company];`
  line
  line `(zi) State Bank of India means the State Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the State`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(zj) subsidiary bank shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (k) of section 2 of the State`
  line `Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959).`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Indian Contract Act,`
  line `1872 (9 of 1872) or the transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882) or the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956) or the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act 1992 (15 of 1992) shall have the same`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for securitisation company or reconstruction company (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  line
  line `4.Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 162, for any person who (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 162, ibid., for and includes a person who (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for securitisation company or reconstruction company (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (ha) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (j) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for 'securitisation company or reconstruction company (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for qualified institutional buyer (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `15. Omitted by Act 44 of 2016, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `16. Subs. by s. 3,ibid.,for securitisation company or reconstruction company (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `17.Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 162, for the Board appointed by any company (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for qualified institutional buyers (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `19. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (zd) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `20. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (zf) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
