  line `21. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for securitisation company or reconstruction company (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `22. Subs. by s. 3,ibid.,for qualified institutional buyer (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (20642)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Registration of asset reconstruction companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20642&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `3. Registration of ^1[asset reconstruction companies].--(1) No ^2[asset reconstruction company] shall`
  line `commence or carry on the business of securitisation or asset reconstruction without--`
  line
  line `(a) obtaining a certificate of registration granted under this section; and`
  line
  line `^3[(b) having net owned fund of not less than two crore rupees or such other higher amount as the`
  line `Reserve Bank, may, by notification, specify;]`
  line
  line `Provided that the Reserve Bank may, by notification, specify different amounts of owned fund for`
  line `different class or classes of ^2[asset reconstruction companies]:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a ^1[asset reconstruction company], existing on the commencement of this Act,`
  line `shall make an application for registration to the Reserve Bank before the expiry of six months from such`
  line `commencement and notwithstanding anything contained in this sub-section may continue to carry on the`
  line `business of securitisation or asset reconstruction until a certificate of registration is granted to it or, as the`
  line `case may be, rejection of application for registration is communicated to it.`
  line
  line `(2) Every ^1[asset reconstruction company] shall make an application for registration to the Reserve`
  line `Bank in such form and manner as it may specify.`
  line
  line `(3) The Reserve Bank may, for the purpose of considering the application for registration of a ^1[asset reconstruction company] to commence or carry on the business of securitisation or asset reconstruction, as`
  line `the case may be, require to be satisfied, by an inspection of records or books of such ^1[asset reconstruction`
  line `company], or otherwise, that the following conditions are fulfilled, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the ^1[asset reconstruction company] has not incurred losses in any of the three preceding`
  line `financial years;`
  line
  line `(b) that such ^1[asset reconstruction company] has made adequate arrangements for realisation of the financial assets acquired for the purpose of securitisation or asset reconstruction and shall be able`
  line `to pay periodical returns and redeem on respective due dates on the investments made in the company`
  line `by the ^4[qualified buyers]or other persons;`
  line
  line `(c) that the directors of ^1[asset reconstruction company] have adequate professional experience in`
  line `matters related to finance, securitisation and reconstruction;`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(e) that any of its directors has not been convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `^6[(f) that a sponsor of an asset reconstruction company is a fit and proper person in accordance`
  line `with the criteria as may be specified in the guidelines issued by the Reserve Bank for such persons;]`
  line
  line `(g) that ^1[asset reconstruction company] has complied with or is in a position to comply with`
  line `prudential norms specified by the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `^7[(h) that ^1[asset reconstruction company] has complied with one or more conditions specified in`
  line `the guidelines issued by the Reserve Bank for the said purpose.]`
  line
  line `(4) The Reserve Bank may, after being satisfied that the conditions specified in sub-section (3) are`
  line `fulfilled, grant a certificate of registration to the ^1[asset reconstruction company] to commence or carry on`
  line `on business of securitisation or asset reconstruction, subject to such conditions, which it may consider, fit to impose.`
  line
  line `(5) The Reserve Bank may reject the application made under sub-section (2) if it is satisfied that the`
  line `conditions specified in sub-section (3) are not fulfilled:`
  line
  line `Provided that before rejecting the application, the applicant shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(6) Every ^1[asset reconstruction company] shall obtain prior approval of the Reserve Bank for any`
  line `substantial change in its management ^8[including appointment of any director on the board of directors of`
  line `the asset reconstruction company or managing director or chief executive officer thereof] or change of`
  line `location of its registered office or change in its name:`
  line
  line `Provided that the decision of the Reserve Bank, whether the change in management of a ^1[asset`
  line `reconstruction company] is a substantial change in its management or not, shall be final.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "substantial change in management"`
  line `means the change in the management by way of transfer of shares or ^8[change affecting the sponsorship in`
  line `in the company by way of transfer of shares or] amalgamation or transfer of the business of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. bys. 3,ibid., for "securitisation companies or reconstruction companies" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. bys. 3,ibid.,for "qualified institutional buyers" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (f) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 3 (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (20643)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Cancellation of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20643&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Reserve Bank may cancel a certificate of`
  line `registration granted to a ^1[asset reconstruction company], if such company--`
  line
  line `(a) ceases to carry on the business of securitisation or asset reconstruction; or`
  line
  line `(b) ceases to receive or hold any investment from a ^2[qualified buyer]; or`
  line
  line `(c) has failed to comply with any conditions subject to which the certificate of registration has`
  line `been granted to it; or`
  line
  line `(d) at any time fails to fulfil any of the conditions referred to in clauses (a) to (g) of sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 3; or`
  line
  line `(e) fails to--`
  line
  line `(i) comply with any direction issued by the Reserve Bank under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(ii) maintain accounts in accordance with the requirements of any law or any direction or`
  line `order issued by the Reserve Bank under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) submit or offer for inspection its books of account or other relevant documents when so demanded by the Reserve Bank; or`
  line
  line `(iv) obtain prior approval of the Reserve Bank required under sub-section (6) of section 3:`
  line
  line `Provided that before cancelling a certificate of registration on the ground that the ^3[asset reconstruction company] has failed to comply with the provisions of clause (c) or has failed to fulfil any`
  line `of the conditions referred to in clause (d) or sub-clause (iv) of clause (e), the Reserve Bank, unless it is of`
  line `the opinion that the delay in cancelling the certificate of registration granted under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 3 shall be prejudicial to the public interest or the interests of the investors or the`
  line `^3[asset reconstruction company], shall give an opportunity to such company on such terms as the Reserve`
  line `Bank may specify for taking necessary steps to comply with such provisions or fulfilment of such`
  line conditions.
  line
  line `(2) A ^3[asset reconstruction company] aggrieved by the order of ^5*** cancellation of certificate of`
  line `registration may prefer an appeal, within a period of thirty days from the date on which ^6[such order of`
  line `cancellation] is communicated to it, to the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that before rejecting an appeal such company shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) A ^3[asset reconstruction company], which is holding investments of ^7[qualified buyers] and whose`
  line `whose application for grant of certificate of registration has been rejected or certificate of registration has`
  line `been cancelled shall, notwithstanding such rejection or cancellation be deemed to be a ^3[asset`
  line `reconstruction company]until it repays the entire investments held by it (together with interest, if any)`
  line `within such period as the Reserve Bank may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "securitisation company or a reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "qualified institutional buyer" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3,ibid.,for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "securitisation company or the reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `5. The words "rejection of application for registration or" omitted by Act 30 of 2004, s. 4 (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. bys. 4,ibid.,for "such order of rejection or cancellation" (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "qualified institutional buyers" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (20644)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Acquisition of rights or interest in financial assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20644&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any agreement or any other law for the time being in force, any ^1[asset reconstruction company] may`
  line `acquire financial assets of any bank or financial institution--`
  line
  line `(a) by issuing a debenture or bond or any other security in the nature of debenture, for`
  line `consideration agreed upon between such company and the bank or financial institution, incorporating`
  line `therein such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon between them; or`
  line
  line `(b) by entering into an agreement with such bank or financial institution for the transfer of such`
  line `financial assets to such company on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon between them.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) Any document executed by any bank or financial institution under sub-section (1) in favour of`
  line `the asset reconstruction company acquiring financial assets for the purposes of asset reconstruction or`
  line `securitisation shall be exempted from stamp duty in accordance with the provisions of section 8F of the`
  line `Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899):`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply where the acquisition of the financial`
  line `assets by the asset reconstruction company is for the purposes other than asset reconstruction or`
  line securitisation.]
  line
  line `(2) If the bank or financial institution is a lender in relation to any financial assets acquired under`
  line `sub-section (1) by the ^3[asset reconstruction company], such ^4[asset reconstruction company] shall, on`
  line `such acquisition, be deemed to be the lender and all the rights of such bank or financial institution shall`
  line `vest in such company in relation to such financial assets.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) If the bank or financial institution is holding any right, title or interest upon any tangible asset`
  line `or intangible asset to secure payment of any unpaid portion of the purchase price of such asset or an`
  line `obligation incurred or credit otherwise provided to enable the borrower to acquire the tangible asset or`
  line `assignment or licence of intangible asset, such right, title or interest shall vest in the asset reconstruction`
  line `company on acquisition of such assets under sub-section (1).]`
  line
  line `(3) Unless otherwise expressly provided by this Act, all contracts, deeds, bonds, agreements, powers of-attorney,`
  line `grants of legal representation, permissions, approvals, consents or no-objections under any law or otherwise and other instruments of whatever nature which relate to the said financial asset and`
  line `which are subsisting or having effect immediately before the acquisition of financial asset under`
  line `sub-section (1) and to which the concerned bank or financial institution is a party or which are in favour`
  line `of such bank or financial institution shall, after the acquisition of the financial assets, be of as full force`
  line `and effect against or in favour of the ^4[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be, and may be`
  line `enforced or acted upon as fully and effectually as if, in the place of the said bank or financial institution, ^4[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be, had been a party thereto or as if they had been issued`
  line `in favour of ^4[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) If, on the date of acquisition of financial asset under sub-section (1), any suit, appeal or other`
  line `proceeding of whatever nature relating to the said financial asset is pending by or against the bank or`
  line `financial institution, save as provided in the third proviso to sub-section (1) of section 15 of the Sick`
  line `Industrial Companies (Special Provisions) Act, 1985 (1 of 1986) the same shall not abate, or be`
  line `discontinued or be, in any way, prejudicially affected by reason of the acquisition of financial asset by`
  line `the^4[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be`
  line `continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the ^4[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^5[(5) On acquisition of financial assets under sub-section (1), the ^4[asset reconstruction company],`
  line `may with the consent of the originator, file an application before the Debts Recovery Tribunal or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal or any court or other Authority for the purpose of substitution of its name in any`
  line `pending suit, appeal or other proceedings and on receipt of such application, such Debts Recovery`
  line `Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal or court or Authority shall pass orders for the substitution of the ^4[asset reconstruction company] in such pending suit, appeal or other proceedings.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3,ibid.,for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "securitisation company or the reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid,, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (20645)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Transfer of pending applications to any one of Debts Recovery Tribunals in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20645&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A.Transfer of pending applications to any one of Debts Recovery Tribunals in certain`
  line `cases.-- (1) If any financial asset, of a borrower acquired by a ^2[asset reconstruction company], comprise`
  line `of secured debts of more than one bank or financial institution for recovery of which such banks or`
  line `financial institutions has filed applications before two or more Debts Recovery Tribunals the ^2[asset reconstruction company]may file an application to the Appellate Tribunal having jurisdiction over any of`
  line `such Tribunals in which such applications are pending for transfer of all pending applications to any one`
  line `of the Debts Recovery Tribunals as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of such application for transfer of all pending applications under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties to the application an opportunity of being heard, pass an`
  line `order for transfer of the pending applications to any one of the Debts Recovery Tribunals.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and Financial`
  line `Institutions Act, 1993 (51 of 1993), any order passed by the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (2)`
  line `shall be binding on all the Debts Recovery Tribunals referred to in sub-section (1) as if such order had`
  line `been passed by the Appellate Tribunal having jurisdiction on each such Debts Recovery Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) Any recovery certificate, issued by the Debts Recovery Tribunal to which all the pending`
  line `applications are transferred under sub-section(2), shall be executed in accordance with the provisions`
  line `contained in sub-section (23) of section 19 and other provisions of the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks`
  line `and Financial Institutions Act, 1993 (51 of 1993)shall, accordingly, apply to such execution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 5 (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (20646)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Notice to obligor and discharge of obligation of such obligor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20646&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bank or financial`
  line `institution may, if it considers appropriate, give a notice of acquisition of financial assets by any ^1[asset reconstruction company], to the concerned obligor and any other concerned person and to the concerned`
  line `registering authority (including Registrar of Companies) in whose jurisdiction the mortgage, charge,`
  line `hypothecation, assignment or other interest created on the financial assets had been registered.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a notice of acquisition of financial asset under sub-section (1) is given by a bank or`
  line `financial institution, the obligor, on receipt of such notice, shall make payment to the concerned ^1[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be, and payment made to such company in discharge of any of`
  line `the obligations in relation to the financial asset specified in the notice shall be a full discharge to the`
  line `obligor making the payment from all liability in respect of such payment.`
  line
  line `(3) Where no notice of acquisition of financial asset under sub-section (1) is given by any bank or`
  line `financial institution, any money or other properties subsequently received by the bank or financial`
  line `institution, shall constitute monies or properties held in trust for the benefit of and on behalf of the ^1[asset`
  line `reconstruction company], as the case may be, and such bank or financial institution shall hold such`
  line `payment or property which shall forthwith be made over or delivered to ^1[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be, or its agent duly authorised in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (20647)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Issue of security by raising of receipts or funds by asset reconstruction company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20647&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `7. Issue of security by raising of receipts or funds by ^1[asset reconstruction company].--(1)`
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), the Securities`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) and the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992`
  line `(15 of 1992), any ^1[asset reconstruction company], may, after acquisition of any financial asset under subsection`
  line `(1) of section 5, offer security receipts to qualified institute buyers ^2[or such other category of`
  line `investors including non-institutional investors as may be specified by the Reserve Bank in consultation`
  line `with the Board, from time to time,] for subscription in accordance with the provisions of those Acts.`
  line
  line `(2) A ^3[asset reconstruction company] may raise funds from the ^4`
  line `[qualified buyers] by formulating`
  line `schemes for acquiring financial assets and shall keep and maintain separate and distinct accounts in`
  line `respect of each such scheme for every financial asset acquired out of investments made by a ^4[qualified`
  line `buyer] and ensure that realisations of such financial asset is held and applied towards redemption of`
  line `investments and payment of returns assured on such investments under the relevant scheme.`
  line
  line `^5[(2A) (a) The scheme for the purpose of offering security receipts under sub-section (1) or raising`
  line `funds under sub-section (2), may be in the nature of a trust to be managed by the ^3[asset reconstruction`
  line `company], and the ^3[asset reconstruction company] shall hold the assets so acquired or the funds so raised for acquiring the assets, in trust for the benefit of the ^4[qualified buyers] holding the security receipts or`
  line `from whom the funds are raised.`
  line
  line `(b) The provisions of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882) shall, except in so far as they are`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, apply with respect to the trust referred to in clause (a) above.]`
  line
  line `(3) In the event of non-realisation under sub-section (2) of financial assets, the ^4[qualified buyers] of a`
  line `^3[asset reconstruction company], holding security receipts of not less than seventy-five per cent. of the`
  line `total value of the ^6[security receipts issued under a scheme by such company], shall be entitled to call a`
  line `meeting of all the ^4[qualified buyers]and every resolution passed in such meeting shall be binding on the`
  line company.
  line
  line `(4) The ^4[qualified buyers] shall, at a meeting called under sub-section (3), follow the same`
  line `procedure, as nearly as possible as is followed at meetings of the board of directors of the ^3[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "(other than by offer to public)" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "qualified institutional buyers" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 6 (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "security receipts issued by such company" (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (20648)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Exemption from registration of security receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20648&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 17 of the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908),--`
  line
  line `(a) any security receipt issued by the ^1[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be, under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7, and not creating, declaring, assigning, limiting or extinguishing any right,`
  line `title or interest, to or in immovable property except in so far as it entitles the holder of the security`
  line `receipt to an undivided interest afforded by a registered instrument; or`
  line
  line `(b) any transfer of security receipts, shall not require compulsory registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (20649)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Measures for assets reconstruction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 8, for section 9 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20649&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Measures for assets reconstruction.-- (1)Without prejudice to the provisions contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, an asset reconstruction company may, for the purposes of asset`
  line `reconstruction, provide for any one or more of the following measures, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the proper management of the business of the borrower, by change in, or take over of, the`
  line `management of the business of the borrower;`
  line
  line `(b) the sale or lease of a part or whole of the business of the borrower;`
  line
  line `(c) rescheduling of payment of debts payable by the borrower;`
  line
  line `(d) enforcement of security interest in accordance with the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) settlement of dues payable by the borrower;`
  line
  line `(f) taking possession of secured assets in accordance with the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) conversion of any portion of debt into shares of a borrower company:`
  line
  line `Provided that conversion of any part of debt into shares of a borrower company shall be deemed`
  line `always to have been valid, as if the provisions of this clause were in force at all material times.`
  line
  line `(2) The Reserve Bank shall, for the purposes of sub-section (1), determine the policy and issue`
  line `necessary directions including the direction for regulation of management of the business of the borrower`
  line `and fees to be charged.`
  line
  line `(3) The asset reconstruction company shall take measures under sub-section (1) in accordance with`
  line `policies and directions of the Reserve Bank determined under sub-section (2).]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (20650)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Other functions of asset reconstruction company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20650&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `10. Other functions of ^1[asset reconstruction company].--(1) Any ^1[asset reconstruction company]`
  line `registered under section 3 may--`
  line
  line `(a) act as an agent for any bank or financial institution for the purpose of recovering their dues`
  line `from the borrower on payment of such fees or charges as may be mutually agreed upon between the`
  line parties;
  line
  line `(b) act as a manager referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (4) of section 13 on such fee as may`
  line `be mutually agreed upon between the parties;`
  line
  line `(c) act as receiver if appointed by any court or tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that no ^1[asset reconstruction company] shall act as a manager if acting as such gives rise to`
  line `any pecuniary liability.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (1), no ^1[asset reconstruction company] which has been`
  line `granted a certificate of registration under sub-section (4) of section 3, shall commence or carry on,`
  line `without prior approval of the Reserve Bank, any business other than that of securitisation or asset`
  line `reconstruction:`
  line
  line `Provided that a ^1[asset reconstruction company] which is carrying on, on or before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, any business other than the business of securitisation or asset reconstruction`
  line `or business referred to in sub-section (1), shall cease to carry on any such business within one year from`
  line `the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,`
  line `"^2[asset reconstruction company]" or`
  line `"^3[asset reconstruction company]" does not include its subsidiary.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. bys. 3,ibid.,for "securitisation company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3,ibid.,for "reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (20651)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Resolution of disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20651&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Where any dispute relating to securitisation or reconstruction or nonpayment`
  line `of any amount due including interest arises amongst any of the parties, namely, the bank, or`
  line `financial institution, or ^1[asset reconstruction companyor] ^2[qualified buyer], such dispute shall be settled`
  line `settled by conciliation or arbitration as provided in the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of`
  line `1996), as if the parties to the dispute have consented in writing for determination of such dispute by`
  line `conciliation or arbitration and the provisions of that Act shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "qualified institutional buyer" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (20652)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to determine policy and issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20652&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Reserve Bank is`
  line `satisfied that in the public interest or to regulate financial system of the country to its advantage or to`
  line `prevent the affairs of any ^1[asset reconstruction company] from being conducted in a manner detrimental`
  line `to the interest of investors or in any manner prejudicial to the interest of such ^1[asset reconstruction`
  line `company], it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may determine the policy and give directions to all or`
  line `any ^1[asset reconstruction company]in matters relating to income recognition, accounting standards,`
  line `making provisions for bad and doubtful debts, capital adequacy based on risk weights for assets and also`
  line `relating to deployment of funds by the ^1[asset reconstruction company], as the case may be, and such`
  line `company shall be bound to follow the policy so determined and the directions so issued.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the power vested under sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank`
  line `may give directions to any ^1`
  line `[asset reconstruction company] generally or to a class of ^2`
  line `[asset reconstruction`
  line `companies] or to any ^1`
  line `[asset reconstruction company] in particular as to--`
  line
  line `(a) the type of financial asset of a bank or financial institution which can be acquired and`
  line `procedure for acquisition of such assets and valuation thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) the aggregate value of financial assets which may be acquired by any ^1[asset reconstruction`
  line company].
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(c) the fee and other charges which may be charged or incurred for management of financial`
  line `assets acquired by any asset reconstruction company;`
  line
  line `(d) transfer of security receipts issued to qualified buyers.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "securitisation companies or reconstruction companies" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (20653)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 14
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to call for statements and information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20653&sectionno=12A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Power of Reserve Bank to call for statements and information.-- The Reserve Bank may`
  line `at any time direct a ^2[asset reconstruction company] to furnish it within such time as may be specified by`
  line `the Reserve Bank, with such statements and information relating to the business or affairs of such ^2[asset`
  line `reconstruction company] (including any business or affairs with which such company is concerned) as the`
  line `Reserve Bank may consider necessary or expedient to obtain for the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 7 (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_b:
  sectionId (20654)
  sectionNo 12B
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to carry out audit and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20654&sectionno=12B&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[12B. Power of Reserve Bank to carry out audit and inspection.-- (1) The Reserve Bank may, for`
  line `the purposes of this Act, carry out or caused to be carried out audit and inspection of an asset`
  line `reconstruction company from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of an asset reconstruction company and its officers to provide assistance and`
  line `cooperation to the Reserve Bank to carry out audit or inspection under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where on audit or inspection or otherwise, the Reserve Bank is satisfied that business of an asset`
  line `reconstruction company is being conducted in a manner detrimental to public interest or to the interests of`
  line `investors in security receipts issued by such asset reconstruction company, the Reserve Bank may, for`
  line `securing proper management of an asset reconstruction company, by an order--`
  line
  line `(a) remove the Chairman or any director or appoint additional directors on the board of directors`
  line `of the asset reconstruction company; or`
  line
  line `(b) appoint any of its officers as an observer to observe the working of the board of directors of`
  line `such asset reconstruction company:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order for removal of Chairman or director under clause (a) shall be made except`
  line `after giving him an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) It shall be the duty of every director or other officer or employee of the asset reconstruction`
  line `company to produce before the person, conducting an audit or inspection under sub-section (1), all such`
  line `books, accounts and other documents in his custody or control and to provide him such statements and`
  line `information relating to the affairs of the asset reconstruction company as may be required by such person`
  line `within the stipulated time specified by him.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (20655)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Enforcement of security interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20655&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 69 or`
  line `section 69A of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), any security interest created in favour of`
  line `any secured creditor may be enforced, without the intervention of the court or tribunal, by such creditor in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any borrower, who is under a liability to a secured creditor under a security agreement,`
  line `makes any default in repayment of secured debt or any instalment thereof, and his account in respect of`
  line `such debt is classified by the secured creditor as non-performing asset, then, the secured creditor may`
  line `require the borrower by notice in writing to discharge in full his liabilities to the secured creditor within`
  line `sixty days from the date of notice failing which the secured creditor shall be entitled to exercise all or any`
  line `of the rights under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) the requirement of classification of secured debt as non-performing asset under this`
  line `sub-section shall not apply to a borrower who has raised funds through issue of debt securities; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the event of default, the debenture trustee shall be entitled to enforce security interest in the`
  line `same manner as provided under this section with such modifications as may be necessary and in`
  line `accordance with the terms and conditions of security documents executed in favour of the debenture`
  line trustee.]
  line
  line `(3) The notice referred to in sub-section (2) shall give details of the amount payable by the borrower`
  line `and the secured assets intended to be enforced by the secured creditor in the event of non-payment of`
  line `secured debts by the borrower.`
  line
  line `^2[(3A) If, on receipt of the notice under sub-section (2), the borrower makes any representation or`
  line `raises any objection, the secured creditor shall consider such representation or objection and if the secured`
  line `creditor comes to the conclusion that such representation or objection is not acceptable or tenable, he shall`
  line `communicate ^3[within fifteen days] of receipt of such representation or objection the reasons for nonacceptance of the representation or objection to the borrower:`
  line
  line `Provided that the reasons so communicated or the likely action of the secured creditor at the stage of`
  line `communication of reasons shall not confer any right upon the borrower to prefer an application to the`
  line `Debts Recovery Tribunal under section 17 or the Court of District Judge under section 17A.]`
  line
  line `(4) In case the borrower fails to discharge his liability in full within the period specified in`
  line `sub-section (2), the secured creditor may take recourse to one or more of the following measures to`
  line `recover his secured debt, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) take possession of the secured assets of the borrower including the right to transfer by way of`
  line `lease, assignment or sale for realising the secured asset;`
  line
  line `^4[(b) take over the management of the business of the borrower including the right to transfer by`
  line `way of lease, assignment or sale for realising the secured asset:`
  line
  line `Provided that the right to transfer by way of lease, assignment or sale shall be exercised only`
  line `where the substantial part of the business of the borrower is held as security for the debt:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the management of whole of the business or part of the business is`
  line `severable, the secured creditor shall take over the management of such business of the borrower`
  line `which is relatable to the security for the debt;]`
  line
  line `(c) appoint any person (hereafter referred to as the manager), to manage the secured assets the`
  line `possession of which has been taken over by the secured creditor;`
  line
  line `(d) require at any time by notice in writing, any person who has acquired any of the secured`
  line `assets from the borrower and from whom any money is due or may become due to the borrower, to`
  line `pay the secured creditor, so much of the money as is sufficient to pay the secured debt.`
  line
  line `(5) Any payment made by any person referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (4) to the secured`
  line `creditor shall give such person a valid discharge as if he has made payment to the borrower.`
  line
  line `^5[(5A) Where the sale of an immovable property, for which a reserve price has been specified, has`
  line `been postponed for want of a bid of an amount not less than such reserve price, it shall be lawful for any`
  line `officer of the secured creditor, if so authorised by the secured creditor in this behalf, to bid for the`
  line `immovable property on behalf of the secured creditor at any subsequent sale.`
  line
  line `(5B) Where the secured creditor, referred to in sub-section (5A), is declared to be the purchaser of the`
  line `immovable property at any subsequent sale, the amount of the purchase price shall be adjusted towards`
  line `the amount of the claim of the secured creditor for which the auction of enforcement of security interest is`
  line `taken by the secured creditor, under sub-section (4) of section 13.`
  line
  line `(5C)The provisions of section 9 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) shall, as far as may`
  line `be, apply to the immovable property acquired by secured creditor under sub-section (5A).]`
  line
  line `(6) Any transfer of secured asset after taking possession thereof or take over of management under`
  line `sub-section (4), by the secured creditor or by the manager on behalf of the secured creditor shall vest in`
  line `the transferee all rights in, or in relation to, the secured asset transferred as if the transfer had been made`
  line `by the owner of such secured asset.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any action has been taken against a borrower under the provisions of sub-section (4), all`
  line `costs, charges and expenses which, in the opinion of the secured creditor, have been properly incurred by`
  line `him or any expenses incidental thereto, shall be recoverable from the borrower and the money which is`
  line `received by the secured creditor shall, in the absence of any contract to the contrary, be held by him in`
  line `trust, to be applied, firstly, in payment of such costs, charges and expenses and secondly, in discharge of`
  line `the dues of the secured creditor and the residue of the money so received shall be paid to the person`
  line `entitled thereto in accordance with his rights and interests.`
  line
  line `^6[(8) Where the amount of dues of the secured creditor together with all costs, charges and expenses`
  line `incurred by him is tendered to the secured creditor at any time before the date of publication of notice for`
  line `public auction or inviting quotations or tender from public or private treaty for transfer by way of lease,`
  line `assignment or sale of the secured assets,--`
  line
  line `(i) the secured assets shall not be transferred by way of lease assignment or sale by the secured`
  line `creditor; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in case, any step has been taken by the secured creditor for transfer by way of lease or`
  line `assignment or sale of the assets before tendering of such amount under this sub-section, no further`
  line `step shall be taken by such secured creditor for transfer by way of lease or assignment or sale of such`
  line `secured assets.]`
  line
  line `(9) ^7[Subject to the provisions of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016, in the case of] financing`
  line `of a financial asset by more than one secured creditors or joint financing of a financial asset by secured`
  line `creditors, no secured creditor shall be entitled to exercise any or all of the rights conferred on him under`
  line `or pursuant to sub-section (4) unless exercise of such right is agreed upon by the secured creditors`
  line `representing not less than ^8[sixty per cent.] in value of the amount outstanding as on a record date and`
  line `such action shall be binding on all the secured creditors:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a company in liquidation, the amount realised from the sale of secured`
  line `assets shall be distributed in accordance with the provisions of section 529A of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956):`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of a company being wound up on or after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, the secured creditor of such company, who opts to realise his security instead of relinquishing his`
  line `security and proving his debt under proviso to sub-section (1) of section 529 of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956), may retain the sale proceeds of his secured assets after depositing the workmen's dues with`
  line `the liquidator in accordance with the provisions of section 529A of that Act:`
  line
  line `Provided also that liquidator referred to in the second proviso shall intimate the secured creditor the`
  line `workmen's dues in accordance with the provisions of section 529A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) and in case such workmen's dues cannot be ascertained, the liquidator shall intimate the estimated`
  line `amount of workmen's dues under that section to the secured creditor and in such case the secured creditor may retain the sale proceeds of the secured assets after depositing the amount of such estimate dues with`
  line `the liquidator:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in case the secured creditor deposits the estimated amount of workmen's dues, such`
  line `creditor shall be liable to pay the balance of the workmen's dues or entitled to receive the excess amount,`
  line `if any, deposited by the secured creditor with the liquidator:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the secured creditor shall furnish an undertaking to the liquidator to pay the`
  line `balance of the workmen's dues, if any.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "record date" means the date agreed upon by the secured creditors representing not less than`
  line `^8[sixty per cent.] in value of the amount outstanding on such date;`
  line
  line `(b) "amount outstanding" shall include principal, interest and any other dues payable by the`
  line `borrower to the secured creditor in respect of secured asset as per the books of account of the secured`
  line creditor.
  line
  line `(10) Where dues of the secured creditor are not fully satisfied with the sale proceeds of the secured`
  line `assets, the secured creditor may file an application in the form and manner as may be prescribed to the`
  line `Debts Recovery Tribunal having jurisdiction or a competent court, as the case may be, for recovery of the`
  line `balance amount from the borrower.`
  line
  line `(11) Without prejudice to the rights conferred on the secured creditor under or by this section, secured`
  line `creditor shall be entitled to proceed against the guarantors or sell the pledged assets without first taking any of the measured specifies in clauses (a) to (d) of sub-section (4) in relation to the secured assets under`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(12) The rights of a secured creditor under this Act may be exercised by one or more of his officers`
  line `authorised in this behalf in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(13) No borrower shall, after receipt of notice referred to in sub-section (2), transfer by way of sale,`
  line `lease or otherwise (other than in the ordinary course of his business) any of his secured assets referred to`
  line `in the notice, without prior written consent of the secured creditor.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 13.--In sub-section (3A), in proviso thereto, omit "or the Court of District`
  line `Judge under section 17A"`
  line
  line `[Vide Order No. 3807(E) dated 26th October, 2020, the Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Third Order, 2020 (w.e.f. 26-10-2020) and Vide Union`
  line `Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.`
  line `3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 8(w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 5, for "within one week" (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 8, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 5 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 11, for sub-section (8) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 251 and The Seventh Schedule, for "In the case of" (w.e.f. 15-11-2016)`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 5, for "three-fourth" (w.e.f. 15-1 -2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (20656)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or District Magistrate to assist secured creditor in taking possession of secured asset.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20656&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the possession of any secured assets is required to be taken by`
  line `the secured creditor or if any of the secured assets is required to be sold or transferred by the secured`
  line `creditor under the provisions of this Act, the secured creditor may, for the purpose of taking possession or`
  line `control of any such secured assets, request, in writing, the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or the District`
  line `Magistrate within whose jurisdiction any such secured asset or other documents relating thereto may be`
  line `situated or found, to take possession thereof, and the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or as the case may be,`
  line `the District Magistrate shall, on such request being made to him--`
  line
  line `(a) take possession of such asset and documents relating thereto; and`
  line
  line `(b) forward such asset and documents to the secured creditor:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that any application by the secured creditor shall be accompanied by an affidavit duly`
  line `affirmed by the authorised officer of the secured creditor, declaring that---`
  line
  line `(i) the aggregate amount of financial assistance granted and the total claim of the Bank as on the`
  line `date of filing the application;`
  line
  line `(ii) the borrower has created security interest over various properties and that the Bank or`
  line `Financial Institution is holding a valid and subsisting security interest over such properties and the`
  line `claim of the Bank or Financial Institution is within the limitation period;`
  line
  line `(iii) the borrower has created security interest over various properties giving the details of`
  line `properties referred to in sub-clause (ii)above;`
  line
  line `(iv) the borrower has committed default in repayment of the financial assistance granted`
  line `aggregating the specified amount;`
  line
  line `(v) consequent upon such default in repayment of the financial assistance the account of the`
  line `borrower has been classified as a non-performing asset;`
  line
  line `(vi) affirming that the period of sixty days notice as required by the provisions of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 13, demanding payment of the defaulted financial assistance has been served on the`
  line borrower;
  line
  line `(vii) the objection or representation in reply to the notice received from the borrower has been`
  line `considered by the secured creditor and reasons for non-acceptance of such objection or representation`
  line `had been communicated to the borrower;`
  line
  line `(viii) the borrower has not made any repayment of the financial assistance in spite of the above`
  line `notice and the Authorised Officer is, therefore, entitled to take possession of the secured assets under`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 13 read with section 14 of the principal Act;`
  line
  line `(ix) that the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder had been complied with:`
  line
  line `Provided further that on receipt of the affidavit from the Authorised Officer, the District Magistrate or`
  line `the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, as the case may be, shall after satisfying the contents of the affidavit`
  line `pass suitable orders for the purpose of taking possession of the secured assets ^2[within a period of thirty`
  line `days from the date of application:]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided also that if no order is passed by the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or District Magistrate`
  line `within the said period of thirty days for reasons beyond his control, he may, after recording reasons in`
  line `writing for the same, pass the order within such further period but not exceeding in aggregate sixty days.]`
  line
  line `Provided also that the requirement of filing affidavit stated in the first proviso shall not apply to`
  line `proceeding pending before any District Magistrate or the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, as the case may`
  line `be, on the date of commencement of this Act.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) The District Magistrate or the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate may authorise any officer`
  line `subordinate to him,--`
  line
  line `(i) to take possession of such assets and documents relating thereto; and`
  line
  line `(ii) to forward such assets and documents to the secured creditor.]`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of securing compliance with the provisions of sub-section (1), the Chief`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate or the District Magistrate may take or cause to be taken such steps and use, or`
  line `cause to be used, such force, as may, in his opinion, be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) No act of the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or the District Magistrate ^1[any officer authorised by the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or District Magistrate] done in pursuance of this section shall be called`
  line `in question in any court or before any authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 6 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 6 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (20657)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title `Manner and effect of take over of management.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20657&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[When the management of business of a`
  line `borrower is taken over by a ^2[asset reconstruction companyunder clause (a) of section 9 or, as the case`
  line `may be, by a secured creditor under clause (b) of sub-section (4) of section 13], the secured creditor may,`
  line `by publishing a notice in a newspaper published in English language and in a newspaper published in an`
  line `Indian language in circulation in the place where the principal office of the borrower is situated, appoint`
  line `as many persons as it thinks fit--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case in which the borrower is a company as defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956), to be the directors of that borrower in accordance with the provisions of that Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, to be the administrator of the business of the borrower.`
  line
  line `(2) On publication of a notice under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case where the borrower is a company as defined in the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956), all persons holding office as directors of the company and in any other case, all`
  line `persons holding any office having power of superintendence, direction and control of the business of`
  line `the borrower immediately before the publication of the notice under sub-section (1), shall be deemed`
  line `to have vacated their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) any contract of management between the borrower and any director or manager thereof`
  line `holding office as such immediately before publication of the notice under sub-section (1),`
  line `shall be`
  line `deemed to be terminated;`
  line
  line `(c) the directors or the administrators appointed under this section shall take such steps as may be`
  line `necessary to take into their custody or under their control all the property, effects and actionable`
  line `claims to which the business of the borrower is, or appears to be, entitled and all the property and`
  line `effects of the business of the borrower shall be deemed to be in the custody of the directors or`
  line `administrators, as the case may be, as from the date of the publication of the notice;`
  line
  line `(d) the directors appointed under this section shall, for all purposes, be the directors of the`
  line `company of the borrower and such directors or as the case may be, the administrators appointed under`
  line `this section, shall alone be entitled to exercise all the powers of the directors or as the case may be, of`
  line `the persons exercising powers of superintendence, direction and control, of the business of the`
  line `borrower whether such powers are derived from the memorandum or articles of association of the`
  line `company of the borrower or from any other source whatsoever.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the management of the business of a borrower, being a company as defined in the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), is taken over by the secured creditor, then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the said Act or in the memorandum or articles of association of such borrower,--`
  line
  line `(a) it shall not be lawful for the shareholders of such company or any other person to nominate or`
  line `appoint any person to be a director of the company;`
  line
  line `(b) no resolution passed at any meeting of the shareholders of such company shall be given effect`
  line `to unless approved by the secured creditor;`
  line
  line `(c) no proceeding for the winding up of such company or for the appointment of a receiver in`
  line `respect thereof shall lie in any court, except with the consent of the secured creditor.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the management of the business of a borrower had been taken over by the secured creditor,`
  line `the secured creditor shall, on realisation of his debt in full, restore the management of the business of the`
  line `borrower to him.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that if any secured creditor jointly with other secured creditors or any asset reconstruction`
  line `company or financial institution or any other assignee has converted part of its debt into shares of a`
  line `borrower company and thereby acquired controlling interest in the borrower company, such secured`
  line `creditors shall not be liable to restore the management of the business to such borrower.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 9, for "When the management of business of a borrower is taken over by a secured creditor"`
  line `(w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 3, for "securitisation company or reconstruction company" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016)`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (20658)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 19
  title `No compensation to directors for loss of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20658&sectionno=16&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any contract or in any other law for the time being in force, no managing director or any`
  line `other director or a manager or any person in charge of management of the business of the borrower shall`
  line `be entitled to any compensation for the loss of office or for the premature termination under this Act of`
  line `any contract of management entered into by him with the borrower.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect the right of any such managing director or any`
  line `other director or manager or any such person in charge of management to recover from the business of the`
  line `borrower, moneys recoverable otherwise than by way of such compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (20659)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 20
  title `Application against measures to recover secured debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20659&sectionno=17&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `17. ^1[Application against measures to recover secured debts].-- (1) Any person (including`
  line `borrower), aggrieved by any of the measures referred to in sub-section (4) of section 13 taken by the`
  line `secured creditor or his authorised officer under this Chapter,`
  line `^2[may make an application along with such`
  line `fee, as may be prescribed,] to the Debts Recovery Tribunal having jurisdiction in the matter within fortyfive`
  line `days from the date on which such measure had been taken:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that different fees may be prescribed for making the application by the borrower and the`
  line `person other than the borrower.]`
  line
  line `^4[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the communication of the`
  line `reasons to the borrower by the secured creditor for not having accepted his representation or objection or`
  line `the likely action of the secured creditor at the stage of communication of reasons to the borrower shall not`
  line `entitle the person (including borrower) to make an application to the Debts Recovery Tribunal under this`
  line sub-section.]
  line
  line `^5[(1A) An application under sub-section (1) shall be filed before the Debts Recovery Tribunal within`
  line `the local limits of whose jurisdiction--`
  line
  line `(a) the cause of action, wholly or in part, arises;`
  line
  line `(b) where the secured asset is located; or`
  line
  line `(c) the branch or any other office of a bank or financial institution is maintaining an account in`
  line `which debt claimed is outstanding for the time being.]`
  line
  line `^6[(2) The Debts Recovery Tribunal shall consider whether any of the measures referred to in`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 13 taken by the secured creditor for enforcement of security are in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^7[(3) If, the Debts Recovery Tribunal, after examining the facts and circumstances of the case and`
  line `evidence produced by the parties, comes to the conclusion that any of the measures referred to in`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 13, taken by the secured creditor are not in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder, and require restoration of the management or restoration of`
  line `possession, of the secured assets to the borrower or other aggrieved person, it may, by order,--`
  line
  line `(a) declare the recourse to any one or more measures referred to in sub-section (4) of section 13`
  line `taken by the secured creditor as invalid; and`
  line
  line `(b) restore the possession of secured assets or management of secured assets to the borrower or`
  line `such other aggrieved person, who has made an application under sub-section (1), as the case may be;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) pass such other direction as it may consider appropriate and necessary in relation to any of the`
  line `recourse taken by the secured creditor under sub-section (4) of section 13.]`
  line
  line `(4) If, the Debts Recovery Tribunal declares the recourse taken by a secured creditor under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 13, is in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the`
  line `secured creditor shall be entitled to take recourse to one or more of the measures specified under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 13 to recover his secured debt.`
  line
  line `^8[(4A) Where--`
  line
  line `(i) any person, in an application under sub-section (1), claims any tenancy or leasehold rights`
  line `upon the secured asset, the Debt Recovery Tribunal, after examining the facts of the case and`
  line `evidence produced by the parties in relation to such claims shall, for the purposes of enforcement of`
  line `security interest, have the jurisdiction to examine whether lease or tenancy,--`
  line
  line `(a) has expired or stood determined; or`
  line
  line `(b) is contrary to section 65A of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882); or`
  line
  line `(c) is contrary to terms of mortgage; or`
  line
  line `(d) is created after the issuance of notice of default and demand by the Bank under subsection`
  line `(2) of section 13 of the Act; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the Debt Recovery Tribunal is satisfied that tenancy right or leasehold rights claimed in`
  line `secured asset falls under the sub-clause (a) or sub-clause (b) or sub-clause (c) or sub-clause (d) of`
  line `clause (i), then notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force, the Debt Recovery Tribunal may pass such order as it deems fit in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act.]`
  line
  line `(5) Any application made under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with by the Debts Recovery Tribunal as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and disposed of within sixty days from the date of such application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Debts Recovery Tribunal may, from time to time, extend the said period for reasons`
  line `to be recorded in writing, so, however, that the total period of pendency of the application with the Debts`
  line `Recovery Tribunal, shall not exceed four months from the date of making of such application made under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(6) If the application is not disposed of by the Debts Recovery Tribunal within the period of four`
  line `months as specified in sub-section (5), any part to the application may make an application, in such form`
  line `as may be prescribed, to the Appellate Tribunal for directing the Debts Recovery Tribunal for expeditious`
  line `disposal of the application pending before the Debts Recovery Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal may,`
  line `on such application, make an order for expeditious disposal of the pending application by the Debts`
  line `Recovery Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(7) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the Debts Recovery Tribunal shall, as far as may be,`
  line `dispose of the application in accordance with the provisions of the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and`
  line `Financial Institutions Act, 1993 (51 of 1993) and the rules made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "Right to appeal" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 10, for "may prefer an appeal" (w.e.f. 21-6-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2002).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 30 of 2004, s.10, for sub-sections (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 14, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (20660)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 21
  title `Making of application to Court of District Judge in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes
