obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `17A. [Making of application to Court of District Judge in certain cases.] Omitted by the Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E)`
  line `dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws)`
  line `Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (20661)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Appeal to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20661&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved, by any order made by the Debts`
  line `Recovery Tribunal ^1[under section 17, may prefer an appeal along with such fee, as may be prescribed]to`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal within thirty days from the date of receipt of the order of Debts Recovery`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `^2[Provided that different fees may be prescribed for filing an appeal by the borrower or by the person`
  line `other than the borrower:]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that no appeal shall be entertained unless the borrower has deposited with the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal fifty per cent. of the amount of debt due from him, as claimed by the secured creditors`
  line `or determined by the Debts Recovery Tribunal, whichever is less:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Appellate Tribunal may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing, reduce the`
  line `amount to not less than twenty-five per cent. of debt referred to in the second proviso.]`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the Appellate Tribunal shall, as far as may be, dispose of`
  line `the appeal in accordance with the provisions of the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and Financial`
  line `Institutions Act, 1993 (51 of 1993) and rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 12, for "under section 17, may prefer an appeal" (w.e.f. 21-6-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (20662)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 23
  title `Validation of fees levied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604&sectionId=20662&sectionno=18A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00037_200254_1517807324604
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Validation of fees levied.--Any fee levied and collected for preferring, before the`
  line `commencement of the Enforcement of Security Interest and Recovery of Debts Laws (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2004, an appeal to the Debts Recovery Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal under this Act, shall be deemed`
  line `always to have been levied and collected in accordance with law as if the amendments made to sections`
  line `17 and 18 of this Act by sections 10 and 12 of the said Act were in force at all material times.]`
